The paper proposes a centralized algorithm for multi-robot path planning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm also utilizes heuristics such as path diversification and optimal sub-problem solution databases, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of optimization techniques, which could fall under the category of mathematical optimization (cs.MA) or machine learning (cs.LG).
